description._content: Catalog #: 15_001730 Title: Savoia Marchetti S.65 ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Another radical design concept was the Savoia Marchetti S.65. Utilizing a central fuselage ""pod"" that incorporated two Isotta-Fraschini V-12 engines with a very small cockpit between, the aircraft never flew in the race due to many mechanical problems. Development continued back in Italy, but a problem with longitudinal instability resulted in the fatal crash which claimed the life of W/O Thomaso Dal Molin.
